Volume = {70},
Pages = {1-6},
Abstract = {The ever increasing number of cyber attacks requires the cyber security
   and forensic specialists to detect, analyze and defend against the cyber
   threats in almost real-time. In practice, timely dealing with such a
   large number of attacks is not possible without deeply perusing the
   attack features and taking corresponding intelligent defensive
   actions-this in essence defines cyber threat intelligence notion.
   However, such an intelligence would not be possible without the aid of
   artificial intelligence, machine learning and advanced data mining
   techniques to collect, analyse, and interpret cyber attack evidences. In
   this introductory chapter we first discuss the notion of cyber threat
   intelligence and its main challenges and opportunities, and then briefly
   introduce the chapters of the book which either address the identified
   challenges or present opportunistic solutions to provide threat
   intelligence.},
