Month = {JUN},
Abstract = {This essay and review on criminal network analysis provides an
   introduction to the special issue ``Human Capital and Social Capital in
   Criminal Networks{''}. It traces the history of the application of
   network analysis in the study of organized crime since the early 1970s.
   It argues that while criminal network analysis has brought a new level
   of methodological rigor to the study of organized crime, a number of
   limitations have become apparent. These include the problem of missing
   data and the challenges encountered in adequately capturing latent
   structures, individual characteristics of network members and
   socio-ecological conditions.},
