   AUG 28-31, 2018},
Organization = {Dalhousie Univ, Fac Comp Sci; HP; Adobe; Dash Hudson; PDF Assoc; FXPAL},
Abstract = {We present some results from a joint project between HP Labs, Cardiff
   University and Dyfed Powys Police on predictive policing. Applications
   of the various techniques from recommender systems and text mining to
   the problem of crime patterns recognition are demonstrated. Our main
   idea is to consider crime records for different regions and time period
   as a corpus of text documents with words being crime types. We apply
   tools from NLP and text documents classifications to analyse different
   regions in time and space. We evaluate performance of several measures
   of similarity for texts and documents clustering algorithms.},
