Abstract = {We present a new system, VISFAN, for the visual analysis of financial
   activity networks. It supports the analyst with effective tools to
   discover financial crimes, like money laundering and frauds. If compared
   with other existing systems and methodologies for the analysis of
   criminal networks, VISFAN presents the following main novelties: (i) It
   combines bottom-up and top-down interaction paradigms for the visual
   exploration of complex networks; (ii) It makes it possible to mix
   automatic and manual clustering; (iii) It allows the analyst to
   interactively customize the dimensions of each cluster region and to
   apply different geometric constraints on the layout. VISFAN also
   implements several tools for social network analysis other than
   clustering. For example, it computes several indices to measure the
   centrality of each actor in the network.},
