Abstract = {Making design choices for big data systems is not trivial. If not
   planned out efficiently, keeping in mind the practical requirements,
   there's a possibility that the deployed system can lack important
   features to match up the application or it may contain
   over-sophisticated methods that incurs a large cost, but little increase
   in the efficiency, output. To equip the end user towards wise design
   choices, we have proposed a decision support framework for big data
   systems that can evaluate the suitability over numerous design
