Note = {4th International Conference on Agents and Artificial Intelligence,
   PORTUGAL, FEB 06-08, 2012},
Abstract = {Storing digital data is increasingly affordable and attractive for many
   organizations, thus allowing longitudinal postum analysis of events and
   for identifying trends that may hold interest for predicting future
   scenarios. Results of manual data analysis suffer from high time
   consumption and human error due to the complexity or volume of data.
   Responding to this, our study explores advances in artificial
   intelligence techniques by presenting experiences from the iterative
   development of a prototype that assists intelligence officers in
   identifying trends in serial crimes. This study contributes by
   illustrating the first steps that may be taken towards diffusing
   advances in artificial intelligence into a practice area serving the
   general public.},
