Abstract = {The evolution of processors and algorithms addresses the needs of
   digitally transforming various fields of the public sector. Greece, in
   particular, shows ascending trends in digitization, especially in the
   last five years, where many State Services moved from bureaucratic
   inefficient processes to using state-of-the-art Information Systems.
   This is not the case in the Greek State Forensic Services - SFS, where
   the outdated procedures along with the limited to zero digitization
   result in major delays of the requested Medical Forensic Orders.
   Research in the fields of Distributed Information Systems and Artificial
   Intelligence concludes that such technologies play a vital role in
   achieving optimal digital transformation with enhanced user experience.
   This work highlights the development of a novel Web-Based Information
   System For Medical Forensics incorporating forensic case management,
   data input via mobile equipment and report compilation with AI
   assistance, making processes more efficient and accelerating the
   delivery of Justice.},
